# Database Rules

## Tables Already Created In Supabase — Do Not Recreate
user_profile, subjects, subtopics, platforms, projects,
tasks, daily_logs, topic_levels, study_questions,
study_attempts, job_applications

## Key Relationships
```
subjects → subtopics (subject_id FK)
tasks → projects, subjects, subtopics, platforms (all nullable FKs)
topic_levels → subjects + subtopics (both required)
study_questions → subjects + subtopics
study_attempts → study_questions
job_applications → standalone (no FK)
daily_logs → unique on (user_id, log_date)
```

## UUID Fields
All id fields are UUID. In Pydantic schemas use:
```python
from uuid import UUID
id: UUID
user_id: UUID
```

## Timestamps
All created_at/updated_at are TIMESTAMP in DB.
In Pydantic use: `from datetime import datetime` → `created_at: datetime`

## Nullable Fields In Tasks
subject_id, subtopic_id, platform_id, problem_name are nullable.
Only populated when task_type = "study".
In Pydantic: `Optional[UUID] = None`

## Status Enums
tasks.status: "today" | "done" | "backlog"
tasks.task_type: "study" | "general"
job_applications.status: "Applied" | "Screening" | "Interview" | "Offer" | "Rejected"
study_questions.difficulty_level: "beginner" | "intermediate" | "advanced"

## topic_levels Score Range
numerical_score: FLOAT between 1.0 and 10.0
streak: INTEGER (resets to 0 on wrong answer)

## Never
- Never CREATE TABLE — all tables exist
- Never ALTER TABLE without explicit instruction
- Never use ORM migrations — direct Supabase client only
